lay in the formation of our personalities. Of special note is Russon's provocative assessment of the economic and political contexts of contemporary adult life and the distinctive problems they pose. Engaging and accessible, Adult Life is for anyone seeking the profound lessons our human culture has learned about living well.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aAdulthoodxPhilosophy. 0aAgingxPhilosophy. 0aSelf (Philosophy). 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Phenomenology. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy of Psychology. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Social Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2020z978311149149340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847952140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438479521423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438479521/original  a978-3-11-149149-3  SUNY Press eBook Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles